{
  "_id": "0BNnWrtKFl3cfMjL",
  "name": "Strike of the Giants",
  "type": "feat",
  "system": {
    "source": {
      "custom": "",
      "book": "BGG",
      "page": "19",
      "license": "",
      "rules": "2014",
      "revision": 1
    },
    "description": {
      "value": "<div><hr /><div>\n\t\t\t\t<p><i>Prerequisites: Martial Proficiency or @background[Giant Foundling|BGG]</i></p>\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>You have absorbed primeval magic that gives you an echo of the might of giants. When you take this feat, choose one of the benefits listed below. Once per turn, when you hit a target with a melee weapon attack or a ranged weapon attack using a thrown weapon, you can imbue the attack with an additional effect depending on the benefit you chose:</p><div data-roll-name-ancestor=\"Cloud Strike\" class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"1\"> <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">Cloud Strike.</span></span> The target takes an extra [[/damage 1d4 type=thunder]] damage. If the target is a creature, it must succeed on a Wisdom saving throw, or you become invisible to it until the start of your next turn or until immediately after you make an attack roll or cast a spell.</p></div><div data-roll-name-ancestor=\"Fire Strike\" class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"2\"> <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">Fire Strike.</span></span> The target takes an extra [[/damage 1d10 type=fire]] damage.</p></div><div data-roll-name-ancestor=\"Frost Strike\" class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"3\"> <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">Frost Strike.</span></span> The target takes an extra [[/damage 1d6 type=cold]] damage. If the target is a creature, it must succeed on a Constitution saving throw, or its speed is reduced to 0 until the start of your next turn.</p></div><div data-roll-name-ancestor=\"Hill Strike\" class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"4\"> <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">Hill Strike.</span></span> The target takes an extra [[/damage 1d6]] damage of the weapon's type. If the target is a creature, it must succeed on a Strength saving throw or have the prone condition.</p></div><div data-roll-name-ancestor=\"Stone Strike\" class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"5\"> <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">Stone Strike.</span></span> The target takes an extra [[/damage 1d6 type=force]] damage. If the target is a creature, it must succeed on a Strength saving throw or be pushed 10 feet from you in a straight line.</p></div><div data-roll-name-ancestor=\"Storm Strike\" class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"6\"> <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">Storm Strike.</span></span> The target takes an extra [[/damage 1d6 type=lightning]] damage. If the target is a creature, it must succeed on a Constitution saving throw, or it has disadvantage on attack rolls until the start of your next turn.</p><p>The saving throw DC for these effects equals 8 + your proficiency bonus + your Strength or Constitution modifier.</p><p>You can use this feat a number of times equal to your proficiency bonus, and you regain all expended uses when you finish a long rest.</p></div></div>\n\t\t\t</div></div>",
      "chat": ""
    },
